<preface id="preface" xreflabel="preface">
 <title>Preface</title>

 <para>
  The main purpose of the APBS Roll is to install and configure the
  <ulink url="http://apbs.sourceforge.net/">APBS</ulink> package on
  <ulink
  url="http://www.rocksclusters.org">Rocks</ulink> clusters.
 </para>

 <para>
  <ulink url="http://apbs.sourceforge.net/">APBS (Adaptive
   Poisson-Boltzmann Solver)</ulink> is a software package for the
   numerical solution of the Poisson-Boltzmann equation (PBE), one of
   the most popular continuum models for describing electrostatic
   interactions between molecular solutes in salty, aqueous
   media. APBS was designed to efficiently evaluate electrostatic
   properties for a wide range of length scales to enable the
   investigation of molecules with tens to millions of atoms.
 </para>

 <para>
  The APBS Roll can be downloaded from the <ulink
   url="http://sourceforge.net/projects/apbs"> APBS download
   site</ulink> and the Roll documentation including installation and
   usage information is available on the <ulink
   url="http://www.nbcr.net/data/docs/rolls/apbs/&document-version;">NBCR web
   site</ulink>.
 </para>

 <note>
  <para>
   The APBS Roll version number reflects version of Rocks for which
   this Roll is packaged, e.g., roll <literal>apbs-&document-version;</literal>
   will contain APBS for Rocks version &document-version;.
  </para>
 </note>

 <para>
  The Roll is being developed by Robert Konecny
  &lt;rok&#064;ucsd.edu&gt; with help from Greg Bruno, Nadya Williams,
  Todd Dolinsky and Nathan Baker.
 </para>

</preface>
